{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Reproduction Steps\n\n1. Two tickets A, B bound to Jira with a `blocks`/`relates_to`/`depends_on` link present BOTH locally and as a Jira issuelink.\n2. Remove the link locally: `rebar unlink A B`.\n3. Run a reconcile pass.\n\n**Expected:** the Jira issuelink is removed to match local; the unlink sticks.\n**Actual:** the local unlink is silently reverted every pass (outbound `_diff_links` is ADD-only -> Jira keeps the link -> inbound `_diff_links_inbound` re-adds it locally).\n\n## Root Cause\n\nSame asymmetric-clear class as parent-detach: both link differs are ADD-only (`outbound_differ.py:983-1040`, `inbound_differ.py:440-514`); the applier has no remove-link path (`batch_dispatch.py:554-595`) and acli has no delete-link method.\n\n## Design (consumes the shared managed-ref gate from parent story safe-luge-nog)\n\nMake link removal LOCAL-AUTHORITATIVE via the shared, compaction-surviving managed-ref provenance gate:\n- Outbound `_diff_links` emits a REMOVE for a Jira link of a mapped type, absent locally, ONLY when the ref is in `managed_refs` (deliberate unlink) — a never-managed Jira link is left for inbound ADOPT, never clobbered.\n- New acli `delete_relationship(from_key, to_key, link_type)` (treat 404-on-already-gone as success).\n- `batch_dispatch.update_one` routes the REMOVE through it, guarding HTTP errors non-fatally.\n- Same-pass suppression: when outbound emits a link REMOVE for to_key, suppress the inbound link-ADD for that target (remove-wins) so local wins.\n- NO inbound-remove dual (keeps links local-authoritative, consistent with parent).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `_diff_links` emits a managed-ref-gated REMOVE for a Jira link absent locally; a never-managed Jira link emits NO remove (adopted inbound instead).\n- [ ] New acli delete-relationship method removes a Jira issuelink; 404-on-gone treated as success; unit-tested.\n- [ ] `batch_dispatch.update_one` applies the link REMOVE, HTTP errors non-fatal.\n- [ ] Same-pass suppression drops the inbound link-ADD echo of an outbound link REMOVE.\n- [ ] Regression tests (RED->GREEN, mutation-checked): local-unlink of a managed link emits an outbound remove and is not re-added inbound; a never-managed Jira link is adopted not removed; survives a compaction boundary."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1782535659137115001,"uuid":"7ada0849-3fad-4f4e-a272-773b2bda637b"}